        "timestamp": "2021-07-06 21:19:35.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(3 comments)\n\nlooks like we could change \"honolulu\" to \"01\" and remove the \"01-\" from all of the file names.  similar for \"istanbul\" and \"02\".\n\nsince \"upgrade\" and \"downgrade\" appear in the full path names, we could remove them from the file names.\n\nI don't see any code to rollback the operations on failure - can do that in a separate review, assuming folks still deem it necessary.  (If not, then there's no point in separating these into individual files.)",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
